<subSubSection id="C3496558FFBDFFB7FF7FB817FAE1F826" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BEC36D3FFBDFFB7FF7FB817FEB4F8EA" blockId="6.[151,1437,1529,1987]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">
Type data: According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFBDFFB7FE67B817FD54F9D2" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[479,700,1565,1591]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref6580" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FD89B814FD8BF9D2" box="[561,611,1565,1591]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
the male and female 
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFBDFFB7FC08B817FBFAF9D2" box="[944,1042,1565,1591]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">syntypes</typeStatus>
are housed at 
<collectionCode id="ED42AE16FFBDFFB7FB0FB817FB1EF9D2" box="[1207,1270,1565,1591]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
, but they were not found there. A single male from the type series was found at 
<collectionCode id="ED42AE16FFBDFFB7FCC7B84BFC3DF9BE" box="[895,981,1601,1627]" country="Hungary" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">HNHM</collectionCode>
and it is here designated 
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFBDFFB7FB43B84BFA8DF9BE" box="[1275,1381,1601,1627]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen has the following data label: [light greenish square] 26 [handwritten]\ 
<collectingRegion id="4997F831FFBDFFB7FBA8B86FFB85F99A" box="[1040,1133,1637,1663]" country="Panama" name="Chiriqui" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">Chiriqui</collectingRegion>
Mocsàry [handwritten]\ 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D50FFBDFFB7FA3BB86FFE1FF946" authority="Mocs." authorityName="Mocs." class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="fusciventris" variety="scutellata">
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FA3BB86FFA7EF99A" box="[1411,1430,1637,1663]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FF2FB883FEC5F946" box="[151,301,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">fusciventris v</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FE84B883FE41F946" box="[316,425,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">scutellata</emphasis>
Mocs.
</taxonomicName>
³ [handwritten] det. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFBDFFB7FD57B883FC9BF946" author="Friese, H." box="[751,883,1673,1699]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" pagination="427 - 431" refId="ref5980" refString="Friese, H. (1898) Die Trigona - Arten Australiens. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 21, 427 - 431." type="journal article" year="1898">Friese 1898</bibRefCitation>
[printed]. Another male specimen from 
<collectingRegion id="4997F831FFBDFFB7FA87B883FA74F946" box="[1343,1436,1673,1699]" country="Panama" name="Chiriqui" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">Chiriqui</collectingRegion>
was found at 
<collectionCode id="ED42AE16FFBDFFB7FE93B8A7FE93F922" box="[299,379,1709,1735]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3kvn-7rck" name="Princeton University" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">MNHP</collectionCode>
with the following data label: [orange square label without text]\ 
<collectingRegion id="4997F831FFBDFFB7FBEAB8A7FB47F922" box="[1106,1199,1709,1735]" country="Panama" name="Chiriqui" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">Chiriqui</collectingRegion>
\ 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D50FFBDFFB7FB05B8A7FEC1F90E" authority="Fr." authorityName="Friese. In" authorityYear="1901" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="fusciventris" variety="scutellata">
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FB05B8A7FAD6F922" box="[1213,1342,1709,1735]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">fusciventris</emphasis>
Mocs v. 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FF2FB8DBFEECF90E" box="[151,260,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">scutellata</emphasis>
Fr.
</taxonomicName>
\ Museum Paris Coll. J. Pérez 1915. Despite its provenance, I cannot be confident that it really belongs to the type series.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36D3FFBDFFB7FF7FB913FD76F8D6" blockId="6.[151,1437,1529,1987]" box="[199,670,1817,1843]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">
<materialsCitation id="3B3B3C8EFFBDFFB7FF7FB913FD72F8D6" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="2284429114" box="[199,666,1817,1843]" country="Panama" location="Chiriqui province" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Chiriqui" typeStatus="holotype">
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFBDFFB7FF7FB913FF17F8D6" box="[199,255,1817,1843]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">Type</typeStatus>
locality: 
<collectingCountry id="F3447643FFBDFFB7FED1B913FE2EF8D6" box="[361,454,1817,1843]" name="Panama" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">Panama</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="4997F831FFBDFFB7FE68B913FD72F8D6" box="[464,666,1817,1843]" country="Panama" name="Chiriqui" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">Chiriquí province</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEC36D3FFBDFFB7FF7FB937FAE1F826" blockId="6.[151,1437,1529,1987]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">
Comments: The critical study of the 
<typeStatus id="54E88871FFBDFFB7FDD3B937FD73F8B2" box="[619,667,1853,1879]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">type</typeStatus>
specimen allowed me to correct the subgeneric assignment for this species, transferring it from 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FE69B96BFE0CF89E" box="[465,484,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C</emphasis>
. (
<taxonomicName id="4C534D50FFBDFFB7FE42B96BFD98F89E" authorityName="Ayala" authorityYear="2002" box="[506,624,1889,1915]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Aphemisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FE42B96BFD98F89E" box="[506,624,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">Aphemisia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFBDFFB7FDC6B96BFCEBF89E" author="Ayala, R." box="[638,771,1889,1915]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref5695" refString="Ayala, R. (2002) Two new subgenera of bees in the genus Centris (Hymenoptera: Apidae). Scientific Papers, Natural History Museum The University of Kansas, 25, 1 - 8. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8484" type="journal article" year="2002">Ayala, 2002</bibRefCitation>
to 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FC9EB96BFCD1F89E" box="[806,825,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FCF7B96BFC19F89E" box="[847,1009,1889,1915]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">Melanocentris</emphasis>
) due the strong apical curvature of the mandible and the shape of the innermost tooth. Considering the distance between the lateral ocellus and the compound eye, 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D50FFBDFFB7FEA1B9A3FE4FF826" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1901" box="[281,423,1961,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellata">
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FEA1B9A3FEC4F826" box="[281,300,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FE82B9A3FE4FF826" box="[314,423,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">scutellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D50FFBDFFB7FD1FB9A3FCA8F826" box="[679,832,1961,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boliviensis">
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FD1FB9A3FD52F826" box="[679,698,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FD70B9A3FCA8F826" box="[712,832,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">boliviensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D50FFBDFFB7FCF6B9A3FC09F826" authorityName="Mocsary" authorityYear="1899" box="[846,993,1961,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavilabris">
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FCF6B9A3FC89F826" box="[846,865,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FCD6B9A3FC09F826" box="[878,993,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">flavilabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C534D50FFBDFFB7FBA0B9A3FAEDF826" authority="Friese, 1924" authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1924" box="[1048,1285,1961,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FBA0B9A3FBC3F826" box="[1048,1067,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B927EAC1FFBDFFB7FB80B9A3FB98F826" box="[1080,1136,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="540">fulva</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC24B22FFBDFFB7FBCFB9A3FAEDF826" author="Friese, H." box="[1143,1285,1961,1987]" pageId="6" pageNumber="540" pagination="19 - 22" refId="ref6117" refString="Friese, H. (1924) Neue formen der Bienengattungen Centris - Epicharis. Konowia, 3, 19 - 22." type="journal article" year="1924">Friese, 1924</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
